HEADWORD: Coronilla
<hw>Cor`o*nil"la</hw> <pr>(k?r`?-n?l"l?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>corona</ets> crown: cf. F. <ets>coronille</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of plants related to the clover, having
their flowers arranged in little heads or tufts resembling
coronets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

